description: Alteration of earlier forslow (spelling presumably influenced by fore-), from Middle English forslowen. More at forslow.

verbs.description: foreslow (third-person singular simple present foreslows, present participle foreslowing, simple past and past participle foreslowed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, intransitive) To be slow or tardy; to slow down.
examples: Furthermore all that are carried with circular motion, seem to foreslow, and to move with more than one motion.

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To slow, hinder, delay, impede.
examples: No stream, no wood, no mountain could foreslow / Their hasty pace.
